Japan said it understood why the U.S.Attacked an Iranian oil platform on Monday.    "Japan, deeply concerned over the increasing threat to theships navigating in the Gulf, understands the circumstancesthat have led the United States government to take thesemeasures," the Foreign Ministry said in a statement.    The statement added that the threat to free and safenavigation had increased after the missile attack on aU.S.-flagged tanker in Kuwaiti territorial waters last Friday. REUTER&#3;